social_posts.post_text:
It's that time of the year where i am truly grateful to see what i've accomplished as an artist during the last 11 months.

Just like many people, i often get caught up thinking on what's missing in my life, and seeing this makes me pause and appreciate what i have. I call this the thanksgiving for artists! 

Anyway, those are just numbers and i know it doesn't mean much but it's great to see the progress year after year, specially as an independent artist.

I wanted to thank every single one of you who believe in me & my music. Nothing would be possible without your love & support! 🙏🏼 🤍

I haven' been very active at all this year but i've been working in a lot of music and i'm looking forward to see what 2023 holds. 

x 

Francisco

AI art is getting scarier every day... 

#ai #lensa #franciscocasarotti

I have no words to describe this feeling... what a tournament, what a final. For a lot of people this is only a sport, but for us Argentinians it's so much more. I would try to explain it to you but i don't think you could ever fully understand.

I went through so many emotions during the whole World Cup and specially during this crazy final match, but now i can officially say: ARGENTINA ARE CHAMPIONS OF THE WORLD !!! 🇦🇷🏆🥇

Gracias por todo Messi 🐐! Gracias a todo el equipo por esta enorme alegria. Estoy orgulloso de ser Argentino! 🙌🏼

TE AMO ARGENTINA 💙🤍

@leomessi
@afaseleccion

New single "Moments" out Friday - Sept 22! 🎹🎶

This piece was inspired by a trip to Cuba earlier this year, where i had a beautiful time and also the pleasure of meeting some wonderful people that i will never forget. 🤍

It's quite different from my previous releases, so i'm a bit nervous yet excited to share it with all of you. 🙏🏼

You can pre-save it now on Spotify using the link in my bio! It will also be available on all streaming platforms September 22nd.

Late to the party, but here’s a recap of my 2023 on Spotify.

I want to take a moment to thank every single one of you who listened to my music last year. Your support means so much to me that no matter how often I say it, it never feels like it’s enough.

After a challenging last couple of months dealing with personal stuff, overwhelmed and away from social media for the most part, I slowly got back on my feet.

For this year, all I can hope for is to continue to share my music with the world, be more present, think less, feel more, and above all make my physical & mental health a priority. May 2024 also be the year where I can truly learn how to focus more on the journey and less on the destination.

Happy new year everyone, I wish you all the best.

-Francisco
